# Premium UI — Validation Workflow

IMPORTANT:
This workflow MUST be executed after:
- creating components
- refactoring architecture
- changing tokens
- updating forms
- modifying accessibility
- modifying Storybook
- modifying docs
- modifying shared utilities

The goal:
- consistency
- maintainability
- architecture stability
- reusable infrastructure
- professional-grade quality

---

# PHASE 1 — INSTALLATION VALIDATION

## STEP 1 — Install Dependencies

Run:

```bash
npm install
```

---

## STEP 2 — Verify Scripts

Run:

```bash
npm run
```

Verify scripts exist:
- build
- storybook
- lint
- test

If lint does not exist:

```bash
ng add @angular-eslint/schematics
```

Then:

```bash
npm install -D prettier eslint-config-prettier
```

---

# PHASE 2 — STATIC VALIDATION

## STEP 1 — Run ESLint

```bash
npm run lint
```

Fix:
- unused imports
- typing issues
- template issues
- accessibility issues
- invalid Angular patterns

Never ignore lint errors.

---

## STEP 2 — Search Hardcoded Values

Search for:

```text
#ffffff
#000000
rgb(
12px
16px
box-shadow
```

Replace with:

```css
var(--pui-*)
```

Never hardcode:
- colors
- spacing
- shadows
- radius

---

## STEP 3 — API Consistency Validation

Verify ALL components use:

### Sizes

- sm
- md
- lg

### Variants

- default
- filled
- outlined
- soft
- ghost
- minimal
- card

### Events

- valueChange
- checkedChange
- openChange
- selectedChange

Avoid inconsistent naming.

---

# PHASE 3 — BUILD VALIDATION

## STEP 1 — Production Build

Run:

```bash
npm run build
```

Fix:
- TypeScript errors
- Angular template errors
- invalid imports
- standalone import issues
- circular dependencies

Requirements:
- zero errors
- minimal warnings

---

# PHASE 4 — STORYBOOK VALIDATION

## STEP 1 — Run Storybook

```bash
npm run storybook
```

---

## STEP 2 — Validate Stories

For EVERY component verify:

### Visual Validation

Verify:
- light mode
- dark mode
- hover states
- focus states
- disabled states
- loading states
- selected states
- invalid states

Fix:
- overflow
- broken spacing
- clipping
- inconsistent typography
- layout issues

---

### Interaction Validation

Verify:
- click interaction
- keyboard interaction
- state updates
- animations
- transitions
- event emission

---

### Accessibility Validation

Verify:
- focus-visible
- aria attributes
- semantic roles
- screen reader support
- keyboard-only usability

Test keys:

```text
Tab
Shift + Tab
Enter
Space
Escape
Arrow Keys
```

---

### Forms Validation

Verify:
- reactive forms
- signal forms
- ControlValueAccessor
- touched state
- invalid state
- disabled state

---

# PHASE 5 — ARCHITECTURE VALIDATION

## STEP 1 — Verify Shared Utility Usage

Ensure components reuse:

```text
internal/accessibility
internal/forms
internal/selection
internal/animations
internal/interactions
internal/overlay
internal/tokens
internal/utilities
```

Avoid duplicated implementations.

---

## STEP 2 — Search Duplicated Logic

Search for:
- duplicated animations
- duplicated hover states
- duplicated accessibility handling
- duplicated focus styles
- duplicated selection logic

Refactor into shared primitives.

---

# PHASE 6 — PERFORMANCE VALIDATION

Verify:
- minimal DOM
- lightweight rendering
- GPU-friendly animations
- transform/opacity animations only

Avoid:
- layout thrashing
- expensive box-shadow animations
- unnecessary wrappers

---

# PHASE 7 — RESPONSIVE VALIDATION

Test:
- mobile
- tablet
- desktop

Verify:
- no overflow
- proper wrapping
- responsive spacing
- responsive layouts

---

# PHASE 8 — DARK MODE VALIDATION

Verify:
- contrast
- readability
- borders
- overlays
- shadows
- hover states
- focus states

All components must work perfectly in:
- light theme
- dark theme

---

# PHASE 9 — DOCS VALIDATION

Verify docs pages contain:
- Overview
- Examples
- API Guide
- Accessibility
- Theming
- Playground

Verify:
- tabs work
- navigation works
- copy buttons work
- examples render correctly

---

# PHASE 10 — REGRESSION VALIDATION

After architecture changes:
retest ALL previous components.

Verify:
- button
- input
- card
- checkbox
- select

Ensure:
new changes did NOT break old components.

---

# PHASE 11 — GIT WORKFLOW

After validation passes:

## Feature

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "feat(component): add premium checkbox system"
```

---

## Fix

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "fix(select): resolve selected value rendering"
```

---

## Refactor

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "refactor(selection): extract shared utilities"
```

---

## Docs

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "docs(card): improve premium examples"
```

---

# FINAL RULES

NEVER:
- leave lint errors
- leave duplicated logic
- hardcode values
- break accessibility
- introduce inconsistent APIs

ALWAYS:
- reuse primitives
- reuse patterns
- reuse tokens
- reuse accessibility
- reuse animations
- reuse forms infrastructure

Consistency now matters more than speed.